## Building a Quiz App in Angular

**Mental model:** Walk an array of questions by index, recording the picked answer per question in a map. Picking locks the choice and reveals correctness; Next advances; the final score is *derived* via a getter. Classic `NgModule` setup, no `?.`/`??` (the build rejects them).

### Step 1 — Index + answers map
```typescript
i = 0;
answers: Record<number, number> = {};
@Input() questions: Question[] = [];
```

### Step 2 — Pick (once)
```typescript
pick(choice: number): void {
  if (this.answers[this.i] != null) { return; }
  this.answers = { ...this.answers, [this.i]: choice };
}
```

### Step 3 — Advance / finish
```typescript
get done(): boolean { return this.i >= this.questions.length; }
```

### Step 4 — Derive score
```typescript
get score(): number {
  return this.questions.reduce((s, q, idx) => s + (this.answers[idx] === q.correct ? 1 : 0), 0);
}
```

**Edge cases**

| Case | Handling |
| :-- | :-- |
| Re-pick | Guard once answered. |
| Next before pick | Disable until answered. |
| Review | Getter score + per-question read. |

**Interview tip:** Keying answers by index (a `Record<number, number>`) rather than tracking a running score keeps score and review both derivable — and makes the strict-mode template indexing clean.

